RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 1 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 74. Maiden Claiming Purse 21000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRUPIA was keen while up close in the five path around the first turn and took the lead in the four path into the backstretch, took back under a hold and prompted the inner leader passing the half, retook command while in hand into the far turn, was roused from the four path into the stretch, and drew clear. IMPETUOUS SOUL bumped with an outer foe leaving the gate, rated in the two path, was coaxed rounding the far turn and swung out to the six path into the lane, and kept on down the center to get up for place. FIVEFIVE SIX CHAMP led around the first turn but was passed by the eventual winner going into the backstretch, settled in the two path and re-inherited the lead passing the half, surrendered the lead again to the eventual winner while shifting to the rail into the far turn and was under urging in the two path at the top of the lane, and was one paced to hold show. STRAIGHT TIME bumped with an inner foe at the start, tracked in the four path, was roused into the far turn and cued right handed in the five path entering the lane, but flattened passing the eighth pole. BLAST THE MUSIC settled off the pace in the four path but was never a factor. FREDDY'S MUSIC stalked in the three path but faded turning into the stretch. UNCLE MARK trailed throughout around the three path.
